WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.400 --> 00:00:02.320
Hey, good evening, family.

00:00:02.320 --> 00:00:04.600
How are y'all doing today?

00:00:05.860 --> 00:00:08.272
Good morning, or wherever you are from.

00:00:08.848 --> 00:00:22.648
I know it's late, but I thought I would come on and pray with y'all for a little bit before you all go to bed and go over some of the things we saw last time so I don't skip today.

00:00:24.088 --> 00:00:29.244
I told Diana, "I feel in my heart to pray for a little bit.

00:00:29.244 --> 00:00:31.670
" So I'm going to go on and pray with the family.

00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:37.120
Instead of just praying by myself, I'll pray with y'all and see what the Lord shows us.

00:00:38.053 --> 00:00:40.940
There's a lot going on in our beautiful nation.

00:00:43.635 --> 00:00:48.160
I talked to a lady today and I want to pray for her family.

00:00:48.426 --> 00:00:55.097
I told her I would, but I won't mention their names because I didn't ask for permission.

00:01:00.746 --> 00:01:07.140
One is dealing with some real heavy pornography issues, and another was dealing with an addiction to medications like opioids.

00:01:10.697 --> 00:01:18.173
Folks, it's an epidemic across this nation—more than what we realize, at least in my circle, until you start coming across people it's affecting majorly.

00:01:19.413 --> 00:01:27.230
It's tragic, but we know who is greater, and it's our God.

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:32.194
We're going to pray for people tonight who have an addiction to pharmaceutical drugs.

00:01:32.194 --> 00:01:39.970
I really have compassion for them after you talk to folks and find out that their family is strung out on this stuff.

00:01:41.702 --> 00:01:42.799
It destroys lives.

00:01:43.370 --> 00:01:54.336
It starts out probably really simple with pain or whatever you're going through, and then your body gets addicted to this stuff and you don't know how to get off of it.

00:01:54.984 --> 00:02:04.719
It's the same problem with fentanyl and all these other things that come across the border, from oxycodone to Lortabs, whatever.

00:02:05.1000 --> 00:02:15.599
I'm not really familiar with all the names, but I know there are a lot of people dealing with this who do not know how to get off of it.

00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:18.213
It's sad.

00:02:18.649 --> 00:02:25.000
Then you have people addicted to pornography, looking at bad stuff on the internet.

00:02:25.500 --> 00:02:31.199
It's so easily accessible in this generation, even more than when I was a teenager.

00:02:32.480 --> 00:02:34.719
It's not just teenagers; it's adults.

00:02:35.908 --> 00:02:45.896
It's become more grotesque with all these different sites and easy access to this stuff, and people are addicted and need help.

00:02:46.929 --> 00:02:49.940
I'm going to tell you, Jesus came to set you free.

00:02:49.940 --> 00:02:51.977
There's an expiration date to it.

00:02:51.977 --> 00:03:07.153
I truly believe that if we lean in and trust in the Lord and get into the Word concerning things like addictions, bondages, and strongholds—major strongholds—Jesus came to set you free.

00:03:07.428 --> 00:03:14.800
That's why I would encourage you to take communion every day, praying for your loved ones who are strung out on these drugs or alcohol.

00:03:15.156 --> 00:03:19.909
One of her kids was strung out on alcohol, and he's getting better.

00:03:22.507 --> 00:03:30.674
I believe it will continue—the manifestation of what they're believing for, for alcohol to be completely off this family.

00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:31.748
It's all addictions.

00:03:34.114 --> 00:03:42.000
The devil comes at you, and if you give him just a little bit, he'll push the door wide open and start to kill, steal, and destroy your life.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:50.389
You think it's just innocent, just a little soft porn, and the next thing you know, you're in something so deep you don't even realize it.

00:03:50.389 --> 00:03:53.467
It becomes live chats and all that other trash.

00:03:54.053 --> 00:03:59.200
I know there's a lot of the body of Christ that needs help.

00:03:59.867 --> 00:04:01.730
We're not here to shame you; we're here to help you.

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:02.960
We want to pray for you.

00:04:03.376 --> 00:04:08.284
I love you and want to tell you that God has a plan for your life.

00:04:08.284 --> 00:04:15.480
It's not to shame you or beat you down and make you feel inadequate, like God can't use you.

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:19.539
No, that's what the devil tries to make you feel like when you're addicted to these pills.

00:04:20.986 --> 00:04:30.107
It starts messing with your personality and your mind because you've opened up demonic doors, and it starts messing with the hormones of your mind and everything else.

00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:31.600
It's very serious.

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:43.931
So we'll pray for them tonight, and we'll pray for anyone else on here who has those addictions and bondages—whether you're bound to pornography, alcohol, gambling, or whatever.

00:04:43.931 --> 00:04:47.390
I just feel in my heart to pray for all of you.

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:04.994
Braden had the idea from watching some of Alex Jones's clips.

00:05:05.257 --> 00:05:10.209
Alex Jones does a long broadcast every day that goes for three or four hours.

00:05:10.209 --> 00:05:27.250
Braden said, "You know, Daddy, he takes those segments on each one of his broadcasts, takes the highlights, and just makes one video on X for 10 or 15 minutes and highlights that conversation so people don't get lost in it.

00:05:29.780 --> 00:05:32.080
" He said, "So that's what I'm going to do.

00:05:32.080 --> 00:05:35.990
I'm going to take the highlight reel of your prayer sessions every time you pray.

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:42.880
If it goes two or three hours, we'll just upload it and do it like Alex Jones does.

00:05:43.220 --> 00:05:47.657
We'll do 10-minute sections of the highlights of that prayer part.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.920
They can pray with you if they feel led to, and if not, they can move on to the next one.

00:05:53.190 --> 00:06:03.771
I'll split the video up over the course of a day or so and put little things in it and make it cool for them—maybe some graphics or whatever.

00:06:04.069 --> 00:06:12.400
Then we'll put it on each one of the channels, and if they don't want to spend time watching the whole thing, then that's on them.

00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:20.440
" He said, "At least we can let the Holy Spirit move, and if the people want to criticize, they can go watch the small ones.

00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:23.834
" I thought, "That's pretty smart, Braden.

00:06:24.479 --> 00:06:29.040
" He thought that through, and I was really proud of that.

00:06:29.040 --> 00:06:32.880
He said, "Hey, Alex Jones did it, Daddy.

00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:33.840
" I said, "Okay.

00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:35.689
" So that's what we're going to do.

00:06:35.911 --> 00:06:36.994
We uploaded one of them.

00:06:36.994 --> 00:06:40.319
We have another one almost done about the roses.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:52.446
I saw a bunch of roses—all really tight-stem roses—this last time.

00:06:53.177 --> 00:06:59.089
It was beautiful how all of these roses, a bouquet of all white roses, were ready.

00:07:03.176 --> 00:07:11.440
They had this beautiful lace wrapped around them.

00:07:11.440 --> 00:07:23.976
You know how you can take tissue paper at the flower shop and wrap them in tissue paper or whatever, and it makes it like a really pretty thing for a homecoming queen, and they present it to the person?

00:07:26.331 --> 00:07:28.480
